definition.value: A C20-gibberellin obtained by selective reduction of the 10beta-carboxy group of gibberellin A14.
A member of the class of triazoles that is 1,2,4-triazole substituted at position 1 by a tricyclohexylstannyl group.
The organophosphate oxoanion formed from choline by removal of two protons from the phosphate group. Major species at pH 7.3.

A C19-gibberellin initially identified in Gibberella fujikuroi and differing from gibberellin A1 by the absence of the OH at C-2 and the presence of a double bond between C-3 and C-3 (gibbane numbering).
A tetracyclic diterpenoid obtained by catabolism of gibberellin A51.
A C20-gibberellin obtained by selective reduction of the 10beta-carboxy group of gibberellin A53.
A C19-gibberellin, initially identified in Phaseolus coccineus and differing from gibberellin A1 by the conversion of the OH at C-2 (gibbane numbering) into an epoxide across C-2 and C-3.
A tetracyclic diterpenoid obtained by catabolism of gibberellin A8.

A C19-gibberellin that is a pentacyclic diterpenoid responsible for promoting growth and elongation of cells in plants. Initially identified in Gibberella fujikuroi it differs from gibberellin A1 in the absence of OH groups at C-2 and C-7 (gibbane numberings).
A methoxyisoflavone that is isoflavone substituted at positions 4' and 7 by hydroxy and methoxy groups respectively.
A macrolide that is oleandolide having a 2,6-dideoxy-3-O-methyl-alpha-Larabino-hexopyranosyl (alpha-L-oleandrosyl) residue attached at position 3.
A macrolide that is oleandolide having a 2,6-dideoxy-alpha-L-arabino-hexopyranosyl (alpha-L-olivosyl) residue attached at position 3.

A carboxylic ester that is the methyl ester of (2E)-(methoxyimino){2-[(2-methylphenoxy)methyl]phenyl}acetic acid. A fungicide for the control of scab on apples and pears and other fungal diseases on a wide range of crops.
A tetrahydroxyflavan in which the four hydroxy groups are located at positions 3', 4', 5 and 7.

A polyketide with formula C31H38N2O7 initially isolated from Streptomyces parvulus as a result of a random screening program for farnesyl transferase (FTase) inhibitors. It is a natural product that exhibits anticancer and antibiotic properties.
A twelve-membered macrolide antibiotic that is biosynthesised by Streptomyces venezuelae.
A N-acyl homoserine lactone that is the monocarboxylic acid amide arising from formal condensation of homoserine lactone with 3-oxododecanoic acid.
A N-acyl homoserine lactone that is the monocarboxylic acid amide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-oxohexanoic acid with the amino group of homoserine lactone.
An N-acyl-L-homoserine lactone having butyryl as the acyl substituent.
